cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.LG, cs.IT 

This paper is about predicting the number of successful cyber intrusions into an organization's computer network using statistical models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper considers the number of hosts on the organization's network, cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the paper discusses the impact of cyber intrusions on organizations, cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper proposes generalized linear models, and cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper evaluates the probability distribution of the count data.
